cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SE 

This paper proposes a method for reducing the risk of cascading outages in power systems using Markovian tree search and risk gradient computation. The paper involves the application of optimization techniques and algorithm development, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with power system modeling and simulation, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
